dataset.how_calculated: Number of fetal deaths occurring at 28 or more weeks gestation, plus infant deaths occurring up to 6 days after birth, divided by the sum of fetal deaths at 28 weeks or more gestation and live births among resident mothers of the area; expressed per 1,000 fetal deaths plus live births. Deaths are restricted to those that can be linked to a birth certificate of a NYC resident mother and are mapped to the mother's usual residence at birth. show_disparities_node.disparitiesPagetext: When population health or the quality of living environments varies by population characteristics such as income or race, there is disparity. One way to visualize disparity is to chart indicators of health or environment across levels of neighborhood poverty. We categorized neighborhoods as high, medium or low poverty. Then we took the median of the neighborhood-specific values in each category. The median is the middle of the sorted group of values.
